{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "In 1982, the United States failed to exert strong diplomatic pressure on Israel that could have ended a massacre of Palestinians in Lebanon.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by scholar Seth Anziska examines the events that lead to the massacre of Palestinians in the Sabra and Shatila camps in Lebanon in 1982, and the extent to which Israel and failed American diplomatic efforts were complicit in the attack; contends that the lesson of the tragedy is that sometimes close allies act contrary to American interests and values.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "23", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Seth", "role": "reported", "lastname": "ANZISKA", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By SETH ANZISKA", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2012/09/17/opinion/a-preventable-massacre.html", "lead_paragraph": "In 1982, the United States failed to exert strong diplomatic pressure on Israel that could have ended a massacre of Palestinians in Lebanon.", "headline": {"seo": "A Preventable Massacre", "main": "A Preventable Massacre", "print_headline": "A Preventable Massacre", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor", "kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor"}, "_id": "50567ed31c22dfde670c8f94", "word_count": "1716", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2012/09/17/opinion/0917OPEDrodriguez/0917OPEDrodriguez-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2012/09/17/opinion/0917OPEDrodriguez/0917OPEDrodriguez-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 588, "url": "images/2012/09/17/opinion/0917OPEDrodriguez/0917OPEDrodriguez-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2012/09/17/opinion/0917OPEDrodriguez/0917OPEDrodriguez-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "588"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2012/09/17/opinion/0917OPEDrodriguez/0917OPE